				<li id="16774078" class="cmnt-root" data="70" data-d="1663293883000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578808/Godslayer's-Greatsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">15 Sep 2022 22:04</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16774078" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This weapon is absolutely nuts in the best possible way.  Like insanely good.<br/><br/>I managed to stomp the godskin ******* with my level 70 dex/faith character and grabbed the weapon.<br/><br/>At first, I was just messing around with it, since I mainly use halberds, spears, hammers etc.<br/><br/>Then I decided to fight the duo at redmane castle and hooooooly ****. This sword MELTS bosses. At least where I am at right now.<br/><br/>The weapon art was hitting for roughly 2k, at +5 and moderate points in dex and faith. I think I am at 30 fth and 27 dex with this character right now.<br/><br/>So as you can see, not anywhere near max potential, and its making quick work of caelid enemies and bosses. <br/><br/>At  SL70, you aren&apos;t really meant to be here, but the weapon equalizes everything here so it&apos;s much more easier.<br/><br/>Dragonbarrow is a different story, but the weapon is carrying everywhere else so far. <br/><br/>It has so much going for it. Its massive, and thus hard skin enemies get smacked around like nothing, its fire inherent meaning fire weak enemies get bodied. It&apos;s beautiful, it&apos;s fast, and most of all? It works extremely well with a dex/faith build.<br/><br/>Not my favorite weapon in the game by a country mile, but it earns top 5 status for me at least. Grab this thing and give it a shot!</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16774078" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16774078" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>71</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16774078"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16774078" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16774078"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16773429" class="cmnt-root" data="33" data-d="1663129840000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578808/Godslayer's-Greatsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">14 Sep 2022 00:30</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16773429" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This is one of the game&apos;s cooler weapons because it competes well with others in its class despite high attribute requirements and relatively low split damage AR by occupying some niche territory. With its unique and slightly faster move set, good reach (third behind GUGS and zweihander), light weight (second behind zweihander) and immensely powerful weapon art that&apos;s slow to execute but grants hyper armor, it&apos;s a stylish option for anyone willing to invest in it. And because its physical damage scales best with dexterity and also has fire damage scaling with faith, a hybrid incantation build can use this very effectively even in one hand with a fast casting speed. It&apos;s the kind of weapon you base a whole build around. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16773429" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16773429" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote 