				<li id="16691633" class="cmnt-root" data="-14" data-d="1653099684000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578808/Godslayer's-Greatsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 May 2022 22:21</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16691633" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This thing&apos;s weapon art is SO EFFIN SLOW.<br/>It&apos;s almost impossible to use in PvP, let alone in a 1v2 or 1v3 situation.<br/><br/>The damage doesn&apos;t even make up for it. Whereas things like the Moonveil can easily oneshot, this thing requires at least two or three hits from the art to connect for a proper kill unless your enemy has like 10 Vigor or negative defense.<br/><br/>IMO, the thing needs a small buff to the speed of its weapon art... Or a base damage buff to make up for its weight and mixed requirements, such that it can slay players with two hits flat out... One hit if they&apos;ve got 10 VIG or somesuch.<br/><br/>Because as-is, it&apos;s a cool weapon and a massive let-down for what you need to dump just to wield it in medium armor alongside an off-hand casting tool and a secondary right-hand swap-out dagger without fat-rolling.<br/>Fromsoft needs to show this thing some love.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16691633" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#r