				<li id="16691409" class="cmnt-root" data="21" data-d="1653097991000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578808/Godslayer's-Greatsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 May 2022 21:53</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16691409" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Some tips for using this sword:<br/><br/>The wind up on the ability, is about the same time as it takes for an invader to spawn in. Meaning, you can stand on them and greet them with an immediate thwack to the face and if they&apos;re not prepared (I.e. NPC&apos;s) the follow up swing is likely to kill them.<br/><br/>Stonebarb Cracked Tear is excellent with this weapon. As it already has decent poise break potential by being a colossal sword (Not as much as other colossals but still quite high) and with the Tear you can fairly easily stagger many bosses which gives enough time to use the ability to blow them up.<br/><br/>When mounted, use strong attacks. The attack speed is pretty much the same as light attacks because of the colossal sword one swing &quot;Combo&quot; for light attacks, but you do more stagger and can hit 2+ times (By hitting with the &quot;Charging&quot; portion of the strong attack and the strong attack itself). Also, it&apos;s hilarious to flip enemies like pancakes with the strong attack.<br/><br/>The ability, can actually hit 3 times. The initial pulling the sword back to wind up for the first swing can deal damage, about 50% that of the first swing itself. So get up close to targets to get that extra hit (Some targets are in fact staggered by burns and so that first bit of damage can actually stagger enemies long enough to land the swing. Things like Onyx Lord, some human enemies etc)<br/><br/>When riding Torrent, be mindful of ledges. As being a large sword, it is susceptible to the bug where running off an edge will not allow you to use Torrent&apos;s second jump. If you are planning to do any platforming (Such as if you&apos;re trying to grab the loot from the bottom of the Bestial Sanctum), swap to something else.<br/><br/>Some facts about the sword that make it kind of a neat thing to have for general Faith builds:<br/><br/>Dealing Fire damage makes it excellent against Handtulas because fire damage causes them to be set on fire stunning them and dealing massive damage (Sadly, using this doesn&apos;t make them burst into black fire...)<br/><br/>Being a colossal weapon, it doesn&apos;t give a hoot about heavy armoured enemies like Miners and will not bounce off them or deal reduced damage despite not being Strike damage. (Note; Some miners carry firebombs in their backpack. These will be ignited by the fire damage this does)<br/><br/>In the same vein, being a colossal weapon, it won&apos;t bounce off shields either, while having a good amount of guard break to boot.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16691409" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16691409" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">3</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>28</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>7</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16691409"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16691409" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16691409"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
